## Simulation Command

--simulate
topology following the CLI
--list-simulation
launch a simulation with the specified
list all the simulations running

## Simulation Parameters

-i, --id <count> specify the id of the simulation (between 0 and 9 included)
-c, --client <count>
specify the number of clients connected to
each satellite terminal
-st, --satellite-terminal <count>
specify the number of terminals in the
emulation
-gw, --gateway <count>
specify the number of the satellite
gateways
-s, --services <count>
specify the services to launch behind the
gateway, the services could be of type "http", service is separated by a coma

## Channel Parameters

-d, --delay <count> specify the delay of the simulation 
-fbw, --forward-bandwidth <count> specify the forward bandwidth of the simulation
-rbw, --return-bandwidth <count> psecify the return bandwidth of the simulation

## Change a running simulation

--simulation-change <params> Modify a running simulation specifying the parameters and the new values
